parameters:
Lize: "Well then, let's get right to it and I'll explain about
combat."

Lize: "Look, can you see something like a black miasma moving over
there...?"
Something resembling black smoke is moving in the distance.

Lize: "Yes, that's a dark miasma born from the void. It's harmless
now, but if left alone, it will transform into a monster and attack
people."

The Black Mist can be encountered on the map and defeated by swinging
your sword. Other enemies will trigger a battle.

The small accessory handed to her is shaped like a sword and emits a
faint, soft light.

Lize: "It may look like just an accessory, but if you wish strongly
enough, it will transform into a greatsword. Give it a try."

Flora steadies her breath and concentrates her mind on the accessory
in her palm.
Clang!!! The small accessory transforms into a large sword.

It's too large for the girl to handle, yet it feels weightless... In
fact, it feels like an extension of her own body.

Lize: "It's the Prism Sword. A magical sword that can only be wielded
by warriors of light, capable of vanquishing the void... You should be
able to defeat \N[302] with a single blow."

Lize: "Right... It'll also serve as good practice for the sword. Let's
try defeating the \N[302] here."

Let's try defeating all the Black Mist on the map. (Use the
conversation button to swing your sword.)

During repeat playthroughs, changing costumes and moving to the
reminiscence room are not available until you clear the Eastern
Forest.
Flora "It'll be good practice for swordplay, let's defeat \N[302]."
Flora "It'll be good practice for swordplay, let's defeat \N[302]."
